                              <explicit xml:lang="gez" type="subscriptio" xml:id="subGH1" corresp="LIT1180Baenta#colophon">
                                 <locus target="#93ra">93ra</locus><note>The Homily by Jacob of Serug on
                                 Abraham (in Text I-8) ends with a subscriptio ascribing the translation of
                                 the homily from Arabic into Gǝʿǝz to Metropolitan ʾabbā Salāma (in tenure
                                 from 1350; cp. EAE IV, 488-89); besides, the authorship of the work is here
                                 attributed (?) to Athanasius (Bishop of Alexandria from 328 to 373; cp. EAE
                                 I, 392)</note> ወረሲ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ማኅደሮ፡ ለአቡነ፡ አባ፡ ሰላማ፡ ጳጳስነ፡ ምስሌሆሙ፡ ደርገ፡ አሜን። ለዝንቱ፡
                                 ድርሳን፡ ዘአጽሐፎ፡ አቡነ፡ አባ፡ ሰላማ፡ ጳጳስ፡ ርቱዓ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ እምጽሐፈ፡ ዚዓሁ፡ ለበግዕ[sic]፤ ወይተሉ፡ ዝየ፡
                                 ተጽሕፎ፡ ዘይቤ፡ አትናትዮስ፡ ጸሎቱ፡ ወበረከቱ፡ ተሀሉ፡ ምስሌነ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።
                                 <note>Here እምዐረቢ or ዐረቢ (“[from] Arabic”) is omitted. 
                                    Cp. the note in<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgbi002">GBI-002</ref>, <locus target="#99rc">99rc</locus>, in<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgms001">GMS-001</ref>, <locus target="#127rb">127rb</locus>, and in<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESaqg004">AQG-004</ref>, 
                                    <locus target="#104va">104va</locus>.</note>
                                 
                                 
                              </explicit>
